# Overview
This project has been created to provide an offline demo of the Red Hat [CloudForms](http://red.ht/2izwErj) (CFME) appliance.
This Dockerfile instantiates CFME 4.1 as a container, and then imports the database dump from the environment in the MBU lab.

# Prerequisites
- Git
- Docker Engine
- VPN access

# Usage

## Build image

```
docker build -t demo/cfme:4.1 .
```

## Run container

```
docker run --privileged -di -p 80:80 -p 443:443 --name cfme41 demo/cfme:4.1
```

## Web Console

After running the container, wait 10-15 mins for the database to populate.

Then, browse `https://localhost/` or `https://localhost/self_service` (self-service portal).

### Credentials

| User | Password | Description |
| ------ | ------------ | ----------- |
| admin | smartvm | Administrative account |
| clouduser | Redhat1! | Customer user |
| cloudops | Redhat1! | Ops engineer |

## Open sh (Bourne shell)

```
docker exec -it cfme41 sh
```

## View logs

```
docker exec -it cfme42 journalctl -f
```

## Stop container

```
docker stop cfme41
```

## Remove container

```
docker rm cfme41
```

## Remove image

```
docker rmi demo/cfme:4.1
```

## Clean workspace

```
# Remove container
docker rm -f cfme41

# Remove image
docker rmi -f demo/cfme:4.1

# Remove volume
docker volume rm $(docker volume ls -qf dangling=true)
```

# Networking

| Port | Description |
| ----- | -------------- |
| 80 | SSL Redirect |
| 443 | Default port |

